1.NAME: zUpdateDate
1.DESCRIPTION: The date (YY*104+MM*102+DD) when the agent has started a new Z matrix.

2.NAME: zUpdateTime
2.DESCRIPTION: The time (HH*104+MM*102+SS) when the agent has started a new Z matrix.

3.NAME: systemKeySize or K
3.DESCRIPTION: The number of bytes (K) of each generated key.

4.NAME: systemIntervalUpdate or T
4.DESCRIPTION: The number of milliseconds of the updating interval of the internal Z matrix.

5.NAME: systemMaxNumberOfKeys or X
5.DESCRIPTION: The maximum number of generated keys that are still valid.

6.NAME: systemKeysTimeToLive or V
6.DESCRIPTION: The number of seconds of the TTL of the generated keys.

7.NAME: systemRestartCounter or Timestamp S
7.DESCRIPTION: The number of seconds that have passed since agent started/restarted.

1.NAME: configMasterKey or M
1.DESCRIPTION: The master double key M with at least K*2 bytes in size.

2.NAME: configFirstCharOfKeysAlphabet
2.DESCRIPTION: The ASCII code of the first character of the alphabet used in the keys (default=33).

3.NAME: configCardinalityOfKeysAlphabet
3.DESCRIPTION: The number of characters (Y) in the alphabet used in the keys (default=94).

1.NAME: dataNumberOfValidKeys
1.DESCRIPTION: The number of elements in the dataTableGeneratedKeys.

2.NAME: dataTableGeneratedKeys
2.DESCRIPTION: A table with information from all created keys that are still valid.

1.NAME: keyId
1.DESCRIPTION: The identification of a generated key.

2.NAME: keyValue
2.DESCRIPTION: The value of a generated key (K bytes/characters long).

3.NAME: keyRequester
3.DESCRIPTION: The identification of the manager/client that initially requested the key.

4.NAME: keyExpirationDate
4.DESCRIPTION: The date (YY*104+MM*102+DD) when the key will expire.

5.NAME: keyExpirationTime
5.DESCRIPTION: The time (HH*104+MM*102+SS) when the key will expire.

6.NAME: keyVisibility
6.DESCRIPTION: 0 - Key value is not visible; 1 - key value is only visible to the requester; 2 - key value is visible to anyone.
